The paper deals with graph drawing, which is a subfield of computational geometry (cs.CG). The focus is on the angular resolution of the drawings, which is related to graph theory (cs.DM) and graph algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the maximum degree of the graphs, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper proposes a method for drawing low degree graphs in three dimensions, which could be relevant to scientific visualization (cs.SI).
